 return slice is initialised with `make([]Event, len(s.events))` before `copy` rather than `append(nil, s.events...)` to make the non-nil guarantee explicit and the intent clear.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01A14aN156WCDYmQhV8uc7s7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01ByGsfKXajNNvE4ZKv6k7Wh","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/metrics/handlers.go.md","content":"Purpose: HTTP handler constructors for the metrics service, implementing POST and GET for the /events endpoint.\nEach constructor closes over an *EventStore and returns an http.HandlerFunc.\n\nTags: implementation, metrics\n\n## Key types\n\n**validEventTypes** — package-level map used as a set for O(1) validation of the `type` field. Accepted values are `\"click-mouse\"` and `\"submit-form\"`.\n\n## Main functions\n\n**PostEvent(store) http.HandlerFunc** — decodes the JSON request body into an anonymous struct, rejects unknown event types with 400, calls `store.Add`, and writes the stored event as 201 JSON. Method is checked first; non-POST returns 405.\n\n**GetEvents(store) http.HandlerFunc** — calls `store.List` and encodes the result as 200 JSON. Non-GET returns 405.\n\n## Design decisions\n\n- Method checks are handled inside each handler (in addition to the mux dispatch in routes.go) so that handlers remain independently testable without the router wrapping them.\n- `json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(stored)` is used rather than `json.Marshal` + `w.Write` to avoid an intermediate buffer allocation.\n- The anonymous decode struct mirrors only the fields the API accepts; clients cannot inject an ID through the request body.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":681,"cache_read_input_tokens":26122,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":681},"output_tokens":63,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":n