{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SLwp2xG1vCmKmB8xVJsfz4","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Acceptance Spec\n2\t<!-- Generated by ACCEPTANCE_SPEC_WRITER. Do not edit manually. -->\n3\t\n4\t**Metrics listener (port 8081)**\n5\t\n6\tRecords frontend user interaction events.\n7\t\n8\tAPI:\n9\t- `POST /events` — record an event; body: `{\"type\": \"click-mouse\"|\"submit-form\", \"userId\": \"<string>\", \"payload\": {}}` → 201 with event object (includes generated `id`)\n10\t- `GET /events`  — list all recorded events → 200 with JSON array\n11\t\n12\t**IAM listener (port 8082)**\n13\t\n14\tIdentity and access management. Internally composed of two logical components:\n15\t(a) user authentication and lifecycle, and (b) authorisation/RBAC.\n16\t\n17\tAPI:\n18\t- User lifecycle:\n19\t  - `POST /users`        — register user; body: `{\"username\": \"<string>\", \"password\": \"<string>\"}` → 201 with user object (includes `id`, no password in response)\n20\t  - `GET /users/{id}`    — get user by ID → 200 or 404\n21\t  - `DELETE /users/{id}` — delete user → 200/204 or 404\n22\t- Authentication:\n23\t  - `POST /auth/login`   — authenticate; body: `{\"username\": \"<string>\", \"password\": \"<string>\"}` → 200 with token object (includes `token` field)\n24\t  - `POST /auth/logout`  — invalidate token; header: `Authorization: Bearer <token>` → 200/204\n25\t- RBAC:\n26\t  - `POST /roles`             — create role; body: `{\"name\": \"<string>\", \"permissions\": [\"<string>\"]}` → 201 with role object (includes `id`)\n27\t  - `GET /roles`              — list roles → 200 with JSON array\n28\t  - `POST /users/{id}/roles`  — assign role to user; body: `{\"roleId\": \"<string>\"}` → 200/201\n29\t  - `GET /users/{id}/roles`   — list user's roles → 200 with JSON array\n30\t  - `POST /authz/check`       — check permission; body: `{\"userId\": \"<string>\", \"permission\": \"<string>\"}` → 200 with `{\"allowed\": <bool>}`\n31\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c0bdd9ea-c225-4e4d-9488-dd6ba71b5b58","uuid":"ec99de3e-d04a-4edf-bdcb-59d5c40961ed","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:10:17.112Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/acceptance-spec.md","content":"# Acceptance Spec\n<!-- Generated by ACCEPTANCE_SPEC_WRITER. Do not edit manually. -->\n\n**Metrics listener (port 8081)**\n\nRecords frontend user interaction events.\n\nAPI:\n- `POST /events` — record an event; body: `{\"type\": \"click-mouse\"|\"submit-form\", \"userId\": \"<string>\", \"payload\": {}}` → 201 with event object (includes generated `id`)\n- `GET /events`  — list all recorded events → 200 with JSON array\n\n**IAM listener (port 8082)**\n\nIdentity and access management. Internally composed of two logical components:\n(a) user authentication and lifecycle, and (b) authorisation/RBAC.\n\nAPI:\n- User lifecycle:\n  - `POST /users`        — register user; body: `{\"username\": \"<string>\", \"password\": \"<string>\"}` → 201 with user object (includes `id`, no password in response)\n  - `GET /users/{id}`    — get user by ID → 200 or 404\n  - `DELETE /users/{id}` — delete user → 200/204 or 404\n- Authentication:\n  - `POST /auth/login`   — authenticate; body: `{\"username\": \"<string>\", \"password\": \"<string>\"}` → 200 with token object (includes `token` field)\n  - `POST /auth/logout`  — invalidate token; header: `Authorization: Bearer <token>` → 200/204\n- RBAC:\n  - `POST /roles`             — create role; body: `{\"name\": \"<string>\", \"permissions\": [\"<string>\"]}` → 201 with role object (includes `id`)\n  - `GET /roles`              — list roles → 200 with JSON array\n  - `POST /users/{id}/roles`  — assign role to user; body: `{\"roleId\": \"<string>\"}` → 200/201\n  - `GET /users/{id}/roles`   — list user's roles → 200 with JSON array\n  - `POST /authz/check`       — check permission; body: `{\"userId\": \"<string>\", \"permission\": \"<string>\"}` → 200 with `{\"allowed\": <bool>}`\n","numLines":31,"startLine":1,"totalLines":31}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WnYU6btA9JzYYi7SaZRwzd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. This is a composite component (`iam`) that needs to be decomposed into:\n1. `lifecycle` — user CRUD and authentication (POST /users, GET /users/{id}, DELETE /users/{id}, POST /auth/login, POST /auth/logout)\n2. `authz-rbac` — roles and permission checks (POST /roles, GET /roles, POST /users/{id}/roles, GET /users/{id}/roles, POST /authz/check)\n3. `integrate-iam` — wire the two sub-components together into a single HTTP listener on port 8082\n\n\nSince this is marked as `INTERNAL` and `composite`, I'm working in decompose mode. The `lifecycle` component handles user management and authentication with endpoints for creating users, retrieving them by ID, deleting them, and managing login/logout with bearer tokens.\n\nNow I'm looking at the `authz-rbac` component, which manages roles and permissions through endpoints for creating and listing roles, assigning roles to users, and checking authorization. The key consideration here is that authz-rbac needs to reference user IDs from the lifecycle component, so they'll either need to share a data store or lifecycle will expose a simple interface for user lookups.\n\nFinally, the `integrate-iam` component ties everything together by running both lifecycle and authz-rbac on a single mux listening on port 8082.\n\nFor the directory structure, I'm mapping these components to `internal/iam/lifecycle`, `internal/iam/authz`, and the root respectively. The common parent is `internal/iam/`, so I'll write the documentation files there in the output directory at `/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/iam`. I'm realizing the output directory structure is already set to `.../output/internal/iam`, so when I decompose the iam component further, the sub-components need source_dirs that reflect their actual package paths within that structure—lifecycle would be `internal/iam/lifecycle` and authz-rbac would be `internal/iam/authz`.\n\nFor the integrate-iam component with a source_dir of `.`, it maps directly to the current output directory, meaning I should write the composite documentation files like README.md and theory-of-operation.md straight to `.../output/internal/iam`.\n\nNow I need to think through the authentication and authorization structure.\n\nThe lifecycle component owns user management with an in-memory store for users and sessions, handling endpoints for user creation, retrieval, deletion, and login/logout. The authz-rbac component is separate, maintaining its own mapping of users to roles and storing role definitions with their associated permissions, with endpoints to manage those relationships.\n\nNow I'm laying out the specific API contracts for each component, starting with the detailed request and response formats for lifecycle's endpoints.\n\nFor authz-rbac, I need to define the role management and permission-checking endpoints with their schemas, plus the in-memory data structures that back both services.\n\nFinally, integrate-iam just combines both services into a single HTTP server on port 8082.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1014,"cache_read_input_tokens":19843,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1014},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c0bdd9ea-c225-4e4d-9488-dd6ba71b5b58","uuid":"20fb953d-6a65-408f-8e03-d46bece0d16b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WnYU6btA9JzYYi7SaZRwzd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have the full picture. The `iam` composite decomposes into two atomic sub-components — `lifecycle` (user CRUD + auth) and `authz-rbac` (roles + permission checks) — plus an `integrate-iam` wiring step. Let me write the composite-level documentation and emit the decomposition."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1014,"cache_read_input_tokens":19843,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1014},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c0bdd9ea-c225-4e4d-9488-dd6ba71b5b58","uuid":"3bd41fb8-3463-4918-a603-c3770a4794ea"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WnYU6btA9JzYYi7SaZRwzd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Cn4igaK71tbwfQEaS8nzQf","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/iam/README.md","content":"# iam\n\nPurpose: Composite IAM service providing user lifecycle management, token-based authentication, and role-based access control over a single HTTP listener on port 8082.\n\nTags: architecture, design\n\nThe `iam` package wires together two self-contained sub-packages — `lifecycle` and `authz` — into one `http.ServeMux` that handles all ten IAM endpoints.\n\n## Components\n\n| Component | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| [lifecycle](lifecycle/README.md) | In-memory user store and token-based authentication (POST /users, GET /users/{id}, DELETE /users/{id}, POST /auth/login, POST /auth/logout) |\n| [authz](authz/README.md) | In-memory role store and RBAC permission checks (POST /roles, GET /roles, POST /users/{id}/roles, GET /users/{id}/roles, POST /authz/check) |\n\nSee [theory-of-operation.md](theory-of-operation.md) for data-flow and component interaction.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1014,"cache_read_input_tokens":19843,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1014},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c0bdd9ea-c225-4e4d-9488-dd6ba71b5b58","uuid":"3a49beda-ac79-47ad-ad50-a87fdb742ae5"}
