{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015HjLsgsr3CZXoqKGLnF9n1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Acceptance Spec\n2\t<!-- Generated by ACCEPTANCE_SPEC_WRITER. Do not edit manually. -->\n3\t\n4\t**Metrics listener (port 8081)**\n5\t\n6\tRecords frontend user interaction events.\n7\t\n8\tAPI:\n9\t- `POST /events` — record an event; body: `{\"type\": \"click-mouse\"|\"submit-form\", \"userId\": \"<string>\", \"payload\": {}}` → 201 with event object (includes generated `id`)\n10\t- `GET /events`  — list all recorded events → 200 with JSON array\n11\t\n12\t**IAM listener (port 8082)**\n13\t\n14\tIdentity and access management. Internally composed of two logical components:\n15\t(a) user authentication and lifecycle, and (b) authorisation/RBAC.\n16\t\n17\tAPI:\n18\t- User lifecycle:\n19\t  - `POST /users`        — register user; body: `{\"username\": \"<string>\", \"password\": \"<string>\"}` → 201 with user object (includes `id`, no password in response)\n20\t  - `GET /users/{id}`    — get user by ID → 200 or 404\n21\t  - `DELETE /users/{id}` — delete user → 200/204 or 404\n22\t- Authentication:\n23\t  - `POST /auth/login`   — authenticate; body: `{\"username\": \"<string>\", \"password\": \"<string>\"}` → 200 with token object (includes `token` field)\n24\t  - `POST /auth/logout`  — invalidate token; header: `Authorization: Bearer <token>` → 200/204\n25\t- RBAC:\n26\t  - `POST /roles`             — create role; body: `{\"name\": \"<string>\", \"permissions\": [\"<string>\"]}` → 201 with role object (includes `id`)\n27\t  - `GET /roles`              — list roles → 200 with JSON array\n28\t  - `POST /users/{id}/roles`  — assign role to user; body: `{\"roleId\": \"<string>\"}` → 200/201\n29\t  - `GET /users/{id}/roles`   — list user's roles → 200 with JSON array\n30\t  - `POST /authz/check`       — check permission; body: `{\"userId\": \"<string>\", \"permission\": \"<string>\"}` → 200 with `{\"allowed\": <bool>}`\n31\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"90951103-4484-400d-836d-3fb9bb5e08a6","uuid":"7abb4985-f635-4e1d-ab01-0ddc429108da","timestamp":"2026-04-05T09:11:54.718Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/acceptance-spec.md","content":"# Acceptance Spec\n<!-- Generated by ACCEPTANCE_SPEC_WRITER. Do not edit manually. -->\n\n**Metrics listener (port 8081)**\n\nRecords frontend user interaction events.\n\nAPI:\n- `POST /events` — record an event; body: `{\"type\": \"click-mouse\"|\"submit-form\", \"userId\": \"<string>\", \"payload\": {}}` → 201 with event object (includes generated `id`)\n- `GET /events`  — list all recorded events → 200 with JSON array\n\n**IAM listener (port 8082)**\n\nIdentity and access management. Internally composed of two logical components:\n(a) user authentication and lifecycle, and (b) authorisation/RBAC.\n\nAPI:\n- User lifecycle:\n  - `POST /users`        — register user; body: `{\"username\": \"<string>\", \"password\": \"<string>\"}` → 201 with user object (includes `id`, no password in response)\n  - `GET /users/{id}`    — get user by ID → 200 or 404\n  - `DELETE /users/{id}` — delete user → 200/204 or 404\n- Authentication:\n  - `POST /auth/login`   — authenticate; body: `{\"username\": \"<string>\", \"password\": \"<string>\"}` → 200 with token object (includes `token` field)\n  - `POST /auth/logout`  — invalidate token; header: `Authorization: Bearer <token>` → 200/204\n- RBAC:\n  - `POST /roles`             — create role; body: `{\"name\": \"<string>\", \"permissions\": [\"<string>\"]}` → 201 with role object (includes `id`)\n  - `GET /roles`              — list roles → 200 with JSON array\n  - `POST /users/{id}/roles`  — assign role to user; body: `{\"roleId\": \"<string>\"}` → 200/201\n  - `GET /users/{id}/roles`   — list user's roles → 200 with JSON array\n  - `POST /authz/check`       — check permission; body: `{\"userId\": \"<string>\", \"permission\": \"<string>\"}` → 200 with `{\"allowed\": <bool>}`\n","numLines":31,"startLine":1,"totalLines":31}}}
