ntly.\n\nFor the `/users/{id}` endpoint, manual path parsing with `strings.TrimPrefix` and `strings.Split` is the simplest approach given the package's small scope, avoiding an extra dependency.\n\nSetting up the handler routing...\n\nI need to decide on password hashing—bcrypt would require adding a dependency, but SHA256 is already available in the standard library, so I'll go with that to keep things minimal.\n\nFor the implementation, I'm planning two files: `lifecycle.go` for the core logic with the handler struct, stores, and all five endpoints, and `lifecycle_test.go` for comprehensive tests. The design uses a `Handler` function that returns a configured `*http.ServeMux`, with separate `UserStore` and `TokenStore` backed by maps and protected by `sync.RWMutex`. I'll generate IDs and tokens using the UUID package that's already available, extract path parameters by splitting the URL string, and handle HTTP methods directly inside each handler.\n\nNow I'll document the API and wrap up the response.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":929,"cache_read_input_tokens":28782,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":929},"output_tokens":40,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"90951103-4484-400d-836d-3fb9bb5e08a6","uuid":"7cbb0398-ad79-4129-95e2-104945b66d5f"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MNbdDBADK67BuawttWVMVQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have everything needed. The module is at Go 1.21, so method-prefix ServeMux patterns aren't available — path parameters must be extracted manually. Let me write the design documentation and emit the response."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":929,"cache_read_input_tokens":28782,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":929},"output_tokens":40,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"90951103-4484-400d-836d-3fb9bb5e08a6","uuid":"70a16a6e-5b78-4160-8168-597b3b23f7dc"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MNbdDBADK67BuawttWVMVQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BTdqZSGWefyiPHAg6adJk6","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/platform-monolith/output/internal/iam/internal/iam/lifecycle/README.md","content":"# lifecycle\n\nPurpose: Provides in-memory user CRUD and token-based authentication for the IAM listener. Implements five HTTP endpoints exposed via an `*http.ServeMux` for registration by integrate-iam.\n\nTags: architecture, design\n\n## File Index\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `lifecycle.go` | `UserStore`, `TokenStore`, `handler` struct, `Handler()` constructor, all five HTTP handler methods |\n| `lifecycle_test.go` | Table-driven HTTP tests for all five endpoints using `net/http/httptest` |\n\n## Overview\n\nThe package owns two in-memory stores, each protected by a `sync.RWMutex`:\n\n- **UserStore** — two maps keyed by ID and by username, holding `{id, username, passwordHash}` records.\n- **TokenStore** — one map keyed by opaque token string, mapping to the owning user ID.\n\nIDs and tokens are generated with `github.com/google/uuid` (v4). Passwords are hashed with `golang.org/x/crypto/bcrypt` (cost 12). All response bodies are JSON; errors use `{\"error\":\"<message>\"}`.\n\n`Handler()` is the single public entry point. It constructs both stores, wires them into a private `handler` struct, and returns a `*http.ServeMux` with all five routes registered. Because the module targets Go 1.21, method-prefix patterns (`POST /users`) are not available — the mux registers bare paths and each handler switches on `r.Method`. Path parameters for `/users/{id}` are extracted by splitting `r.URL.Path`.\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/google/uuid` — already in `go.mod`; used for ID and token generation\n- `golang.org/x/crypto/bcrypt` — must be added to `go.mod` (`go get golang.org/x/crypto`)\n\nSee [api.md](api.md) for the full endpoint contract.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":929,"cache_read_input_tokens":28782,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":929},"output_tokens":40,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"90951103-4484-400d-836d-3fb9bb5e08a6","uuid":"67844dd1-a23d-4c36-a0e4-ded206b27435"}
