{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PJcBkkgcfcTRL5vEhFeFDr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The module is `github.com/cornjacket/platform-monolith`. The output directory is `output/`, so the root of the module is the `output/` directory.\n\nThe lifecycle package is at path `output/internal/iam/internal/iam/lifecycle/lifecycle.go`, which means the import path would be `github.com/cornjacket/platform-monolith/internal/iam/internal/iam/lifecycle`. That seems wrong - it's a doubled path.\n\nBut wait, the subagents that wrote lifecycle and authz were given the output directory as `output/internal/iam` (the IAM output dir), but they wrote files to `output/internal/iam/internal/iam/lifecycle/`. \n\n\nThe ARCHITECT decomposed IAM with components at `internal/iam/lifecycle` and `internal/iam/authz` as source directories, but the IMPLEMENTOR agents seem to have nested them incorrectly. Let me check the lifecycle README to see what the intended import path should be.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":501,"cache_read_input_tokens":28409,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":501},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f7aca593-a67a-40e6-95f5-6d62c7291aff","uuid":"25933695-d717-48ce-b218-baeacb8670f0"}
