arate functions for starting the metrics and IAM listeners, then write a `TestMain` that spins up both servers in goroutines and runs the tests against them.\n\nFor the test setup, I'll need to:\n1. Start the metrics server on a test port (e.g., 8081)\n2. Start the IAM server on a test port (e.g., 8082)\n3. Wait for both to be ready\n4. Run the tests\n5. Clean up the listeners\n\nI should also double-check the actual constructor names in the metrics and IAM packages to make sure I'm calling them correctly.\n\n---\n\nThen I need to clean up the listeners after tests finish. Let me verify the exact constructor names for the metrics and IAM packages so I'm calling them correctly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1274,"cache_read_input_tokens":23807,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1274},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"47ffb4dd-649b-4f80-9094-fd10b5b9797a","uuid":"05e2f2bf-61de-49f2-ba25-479151050fe3"}
